documentType: evidence inventory and chain of custody form
summary: This is an FBI evidence inventory and chain of custody form (FD-1087) for a box of items collected on August 28, 2006, under case 31E-MM-108062. The box contains various items including medical supplies, letters, invoices, Amazon documents, white papers, messages, magazines, VHS and micro cassette tapes, and miscellaneous paperwork from trash pulls. The document shows evidence handling and inventory updates through July 20, 2021.

keyFacts: Evidence was collected on August 28, 2006, as part of case 31E-MM-108062, which is likely related to the Epstein investigation.

The evidence box contains a mix of documents (letters, invoices, white papers, trash pull paperwork) and media (VHS and Sony micro cassettes), suggesting a broad collection of potential investigative materials.
Items include references to '727 LETTERHEAD', 'AMAZON.COM', and messages from individuals identified only by initials (J., J.L.), indicating potential correspondence or financial records.
Multiple 'trash pull' items are listed, indicating evidence was obtained from discarded materials.
The evidence was held by the New York FBI office but originated from or was connected to Miami (MM - MIAMI), showing multi-district involvement.
